B`.text:
*** DO NOT CHANGE! ***

Unless porting InterApp runtime to different OSes
All these settings are OS-specific, they indicate its capabilities and changing these settings may cause bugs or even break InterApp programs!

w_.text:
DRIVER CONFIG:
- 'os' - The OS the driver is running under. For example, OpenMX 10 would have this field set to 'OpenMX'.
- 'ossku' - The variant/edition/etc. of driver's OS. For Example, the Cosmos edition of TriOS, known as TriOS Cosmos, would have this field set to 'Cosmos'. If this option doesn't apply, set to 'undefined'.
- 'osver' - The version (not to be confused with 'ossku') of the OS. For Example, Bambus OS 6.01 would have this field set to '6.01'.
- 'by' - Credit for the person/team responsible for porting the generic driver to an OS. An official IA2 port has this flag set to 'Official'
- 'cli_shell_type' - The type of the CLI shell used by the OS. If not supported (use_terminal=false), this flag should be set to 'undefined'.
- 'fs_type' - The type of filesystem the OS has (flat or structural). If no filesystem is present, this field should be set to 'undefined'.
- 'driverver' - Driver's reported version.
- 'drivertier' - Driver's tier as defined by the InterApp v2 Driver Tier Specification. Can be set to 1, 2 or 3.

FEATURE SUPPORT (true/false):
- 'use_wallpaper' - Support for fetching the ID of the current wallpaper or the ability to change it.
- 'use_volume' - Support for sound volume adjustment.
- 'use_lightdark_theming' - Support for light-dark themes from the OS.
- 'use_fullscreen' - Support for rendering in fullscreen mode. When set to false, the OS is assumed to only support window mode. To make fullscreen the only option, this flag should be set to 'only'.
- 'use_terminal' - Support for CLI input to the OS.
- 'use_os_decorations' - Support for rendering window decorations by the OS for an InterApp application. The driver does not feature support for OS decorations, therefore the app support for it must be handled by the app developer.
- 'use_filesystem' - Support for accesing OS's filesystem through InterApp's FS API.

FEATURE SUPPORT FOR EACH IA2 TIER:
Tier 1: Wallpaper, Volume
Tier 2: All Tier 1 features, Fullscreen, OS decorations (optional)
Tier 3: All Tier 2 features, Filesystem , Terminal (optional)

Cb.text:
This is NOT a functional InterApp driver.
Do NOT use this in an OS!
If you're looking to install IA2 to your OS, find a version specific for your OS.

The generic driver does not implement any system calls and only contains stubs.
